## Milestones (Waterfall)

### Milestone A — Project skeleton
- Expo RN app created.
- Basic folder structure.
- Navigation shell.

**Done when**
- App runs on Android device/emulator without errors.
- Tabs navigate correctly.

### Milestone B — Manual products
- Products list.
- Product form with validation.
- Local persistence.
  
**Done when**
- Add product → restart app → product still there.

### Milestone C — Product edit/delete
- Edit screen prefilled.
- Delete with confirm.

**Done when**
- Edits persist and reflect in meal calculations.

### Milestone D — Meal builder
- Select products into meal.
- Input grams per item.
- Live total calories.
- Save meal.

**Done when**
- Meal appears in history after save.

### Milestone E — Meal details + edit
- Meal details screen.
- Meal edit mode in builder.

**Done when**
- Editing meal updates history total, no duplicates.

### Milestone F — Polish + stabilization
- Search products.
- Improve empty/loading states.
- Edge-case QA.

**Done when**
- No obvious UX holes / crashes.
- MVP ready for daily use.

### Milestone G — AI dish parsing (post-MVP)
- Text input “Describe dish”.
- Backend LLM call.
- UI to accept/adjust ingredients.

**Done when**
- AI output editable into a normal meal flow.

---

## Key risks & mitigations
- **Scope creep** → freeze MVP scope until Milestone F done.
- **Bad meal UX** → daily usage by you is the test; fix friction first.
- **AI accuracy issues** → AI is optional UI layer, manual edit always wins.

---

## Release plan
- Internal Android build first.
- Use for 2–4 weeks personally.
- Gather friction notes → patch.
- Only then start AI milestone.

---

## Post-MVP roadmap (high level)
